cturally stable or actually too repetitive to ever justify live expansion.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM remains correctly out of active hours.\n- The current **04h session** now has **57** tracked windows.\n- Regime split:\n  - `(0.505, 0.495)` \u2192 **52/57 = 91.2%**\n  - `(0.485, 0.515)` \u2192 **5/57 = 8.8%**\n- Bias frequency stayed active:\n  - `|bias| >= 45` in **31/57 = 54.4%**\n  - `|bias| >= 55` in **17/57 = 29.8%**\n  - `<35` in **17/57 = 29.8%**\n- But almost all of that useful-looking activity lives inside the same one-note regime:\n  - dominant regime = `(0.505, 0.495)`\n  - dominant regime contributes **26** of the **31** `|bias| >= 45` windows = **83.9%** of all 45+ readings\n- Wrote new research artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v7i-overnight-monotony-gate.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is the missing filter. 04h is no longer interesting as an expansion candidate just because it is stable and active. It is too repetitive. The hour keeps printing the same midpoint state with the same type of bias behavior. That may describe overnight order-flow mechanics,",
